cs.NE, cs.ET, cs.EM, cs.AR, cs.CV 

The paper focuses on the design and implementation of an elementary memristive circuit for the anticipation of digital patterns, which involves neuromorphic computation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves the use of memristive devices, which fall under the category of cs.ET (Emerging Technologies). Additionally, the paper discusses the fabrication of memristive devices, which falls under the category of cs.EM (Electronic Materials). The paper also involves the use of images, which can be analyzed using computer vision techniques, falling under the category of cs.AR (Augmented Reality) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
